`crates/steno/src/bin/` holds the workspace's standalone binaries built on top of the `steno` lib crate — none of these files are depended on by anything else; each is a CLI entry point producing artifacts consumed downstream (Plover, the nvim plugin, or a browser-based viz page) or a manual diagnostic report.

All three top-level binaries (`build_dict.rs`, `build_nvim.rs`, `measure.rs`) share the same `root()` convention: workspace root is resolved as `CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR/../..`, hardcoding that this crate sits two directories below the workspace root where `dict.steno` and `out/` live — moving the `steno` crate breaks all three simultaneously. All three also call `expand_dict(&entries, None)` (no profile/pool filter) before deriving their specific outputs, and all funnel errors as `Result<_, String>` up to a `fail()`-style handler that prints to stderr and returns `ExitCode::FAILURE` — no panics on expected failure paths (missing file, parse error, collision) anywhere in this directory.

`build_dict.rs` and `build_nvim.rs` share a stronger invariant: both build every output artifact and run collision-guard checks *before writing anything*, so a colliding build never leaves a stale-plus-fresh mismatched file pair (or, for `build_nvim`, leaves `out/` completely untouched). `measure.rs` writes no files at all — it's a read-only comparison tool that reproduces the same `parse_source → expand_dict → build_plain_dict/build_smart_dict` pipeline six times over different generic-arg pools and param-shape configurations to print a size matrix; its `NOPARAM` stroke table must be kept in hand-sync with `dict.steno`'s actual function-shape strokes or measurements silently skew with no error. All three binaries break immediately on any signature change to `steno`'s public API (`parse_source`, `expand_dict`, `build_plain_dict`, `build_smart_dict`, `to_json`, etc.).

`viz_data/` is a self-contained sibling: a separate multi-file binary with its own internal pipeline (comment scanning, tree building, axis bucketing, JSON emission) producing `out/viz-data.json` for `viz/index.html`. It shares only the `steno`-lib dependency and the general "parse dict.steno, emit an `out/` artifact" pattern with its siblings — no code or key-format coupling crosses into it from the other three files.